<HEADLINE>
FT  21 SEP 94 / Power equipment recovery picks up
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Optimism about business conditions is rising among makers of electrical
installation equipment after one of the most severe and prolonged recessions
for many of them, Mr Stephen Lawson, president of the Electrical
Installation Equipment Manufacturers' Association, said yesterday.
Demand in some areas of the UK market for plugs, sockets, circuit breakers
and other equipment fell by 40 per cent during the recession but the patchy
recovery of 12 months ago had strengthened, albeit slowly and unevenly, he
said at the association's annual lunch.
The upturn in the construction industry had boosted sales of electrical
equipment, although construction activity was still down on pre-recession
levels.
