FT  21 SEP 94 / Walker 'freebooter in business world'
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr George Walker, the former Brent Walker chairman, was a 'freebooter' in
the business world, Lord Richard, the leader of the Labour party in
the House of Lords, told the Brent Walker trial yesterday.
Appearing as a character witness for Mr Walker, the peer told the Old Bailey
that the entrepreneur had a reputation as a tough negotiator. 'He knew what
he wanted and usually got what he wanted.'
Mr Walker and Mr Wilfred Aquilina, a former Brent Walker finance director,
are accused of fraudulently inflating the company's profits. Both deny
charges of theft, false accounting and conspiring to falsify accounts. The
trial continues today.
