<PROFILE>_AN-EIUAHAADFT</PROFILE>
<DATE>940920
</DATE>
<HEADLINE>
FT  20 SEP 94 / Observer: Happy families
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
So Ramon Pajares has finally succumbed to the blandishments of Rocco Forte
and the Savoy Group. He is packing his bags at the Four Seasons and heading
for the office of Giles Shepard, who made his exit last week.
As much the preferred candidate of both the Savoy and Forte, he was no doubt
under considerable pressure to accept - perhaps even from his nearest and
dearest. For his daughter, Maria, as PR manager of Claridge's, must surely
have been a trifle parti pris.
</TEXT>
