Bruce, Liberal Democrat tax spokesman, in effect to ditch proposals for a
top tax rate of 60 per cent on incomes of more than Pounds 100,000. Mr David
Heathcoat-Amory, paymaster general, accused Mr Bruce of a U-turn 'rapid even
