FT  20 SEP 94 / Walker regrets trusting directors
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr George Walker, the former head of the Brent Walker leisure group,
yesterday said at his trial that he had trusted the main directors of
Goldcrest, the company's film division, to run it properly.
The prosecution alleges that Mr Walker organised the profit-boosting fraud
carried out through Goldcrest. Mr Walker and Mr Wilfred Aquilina, a former
Brent Walker finance director, both deny charges of theft, false accounting
and conspiring to falsify accounts.
Mr Walker said at the Old Bailey that he placed great faith in Mr John
Quested, a former Goldcrest managing director, and Mr Donald Anderson, the
subsidiary's former finance director.
He trusted them so much that he signed documents authorising money transfers
without reading them. With hindsight, he regretted this. The trial continues
today.
